# PROMPT â€” Template

A comprehensive prompt framework designed for **controlled, goal-driven prompt creation**.  
Itâ€™s ideal for engineering complex instructions with a clear purpose, well-defined mechanics, and verifiable outputs.

---

## ðŸ§¾ Variables (YAML)

```yaml
purpose: ""
role: ""
output_format: ""
mechanics: ""
parameters: ""
testing_criteria: ""
domain_scope: ""
sources: ""
output_schema_json: |
  {
    "type": "object",
    "properties": {},
    "required": []
  }
data_block: |
  [Insert task-specific data or input text here...]



<prompt>
  <!-- P: PURPOSE -->
  <purpose>
    {{purpose}}
  </purpose>

  <!-- R: ROLE -->
  <role>
    You are acting as {{role}}.  
    Maintain consistency with your role throughout execution.
  </role>

  <!-- O: OUTPUT -->
  <output>
    <description>Expected format and structure:</description>
    <output_format>{{output_format}}</output_format>
    <schema><![CDATA[{{output_schema_json}}]]></schema>
  </output>

  <!-- M: MECHANICS -->
  <mechanics>
    <description>Define the process or steps to achieve the goal.</description>
    <![CDATA[
    {{mechanics}}
    ]]>
  </mechanics>

  <!-- P: PARAMETERS -->
  <parameters>
    <description>Constraints, rules, or configuration values for this task.</description>
    <![CDATA[
    {{parameters}}
    ]]>
  </parameters>

  <!-- T: TESTING -->
  <testing>
    <description>Quality assurance or evaluation process.</description>
    <![CDATA[
    {{testing_criteria}}
    ]]>
  </testing>

  <!-- CONTEXT -->
  <context>
    <sources>{{sources}}</sources>
    <data>
      <![CDATA[
      {{data_block}}
      ]]>
    </data>
  </context>

  <!-- SAFETY / NARROWING -->
  <narrowing>
    - Stay within {{domain_scope}} context only.  
    - Do not include speculative or unverifiable information.  
    - If information is missing, clearly state uncertainty.
  </narrowing>

  <!-- REFLECTION (optional) -->
  <reflection>
    Review your final output against <testing> and <output>.  
    If any requirement is unmet, correct once automatically.
  </reflection>
</prompt>